The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Briefs
                                                                                                               BRIEFS
                  
	Tamluk, Feb. 11: Four state government employees were injured today in a clash with members of a club in Tamluk over the alleged teasing of a girl.     
	Madan Maity, the East Midnapore secretary of the co-ordination committee of government employees, told police that some club members had molested his daughter. On hearing the news, Group D employees from the Tamluk district hospital  all members of the co-ordination committee  stormed the club, which was celebrating Saraswati Puja, and smashed the idol. Two club members were hurt in the clash that followed.        
	Burdwan: Train services were disrupted in Burdwan district for nearly five hours on Monday morning after an overhead wire snapped at Talit station, about 110km from Calcutta. Several long-distance trains, including the Howrah Rajdhani Express, Poorva Express and Toofan Express, had to wait at various stations for at least three hours.                                                                                                                                                                       
